U.S. Advised to Face Up to Trend of Times 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the former U.S. ambassador to south Korea and the former assistant to the Korean Peninsula Energy Development Organization, strongly criticized the Bush administration's policy toward Korea, holding that the Bush administration's assertion can not get any understanding of the countries participating in the six-way talks as it is unacceptable in any case.
 Even Pritchard, who was in charge of negotiations with the DPRK in the administration, said that the Bush administration's policy toward the DPRK would get it nowhere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today says in a signed commentary: The reality shows that the international community is unanimous in demanding the U.S. give up its hostile policy toward the DPRK at an early date and take a positive stand for solving the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. The U.S. should face up to the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now styling itself a "superpower". But if it fails to face up to the trend of the times and goes against it, it will lose its position on the international arena and will be forsaken by history in the end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should give up its hostile policy toward the DPRK and conclude a non-aggression treaty with it. This is the only way to settle the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. Any other option but this does not bring any interest to the DPRK nor work on it. The DPRK does not require such option at all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 U.S. unilateralism and big stick policy are futile before the DPRK. The Bush administration should not defy the reality any longer if it has a shred of reason. It is beneficial for the U.S. itself

World Day of Teachers Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) --Minju Joson today dedicates an article to the World Day of Teachers. A decision on the day was adopted at the International Education Conference on October. 5, 1994.
 Educational work is of weighty importance in achieving progress and prosperity of the country and the nation, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality today when science and technology are making rapid progress requires the countries of the world to pay primary attention to the development of the educational work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this occasion colorful events are taking place in different countries to increase the position and role of teachers. On this day UNESCO is awarding certificates of qualification and medals to those teachers who have distinguished themselves in the development of the education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The position and role of the teachers in the DPRK have remarkably increased thanks to the wise measures taken by the Workers' Party of Korea and the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The teachers in the DPRK are highly regarded as career revolutionaries and a trait of treating them with respect and hospitality prevails throughout the society.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's Exploits in Party Building 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- A seminar on leader Kim Jong Il's immortal exploits in party building was held at the building of the Socialist Party of Romania on September 23 under the co-sponsorship of the SPR and the Romanian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea.
 Addressing the seminar, the chairman of the SPR, the chairman of the National Committee and others referred to the foundation and development of the Workers' Party of Korea and  Kim Jong Il's exploits in party building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers stressed it is the result of the outstanding and tested leadership of Kim Jong Il that the WPK could develop into an invincible, steel-like party guided by the Juche idea, a party based on the mass foundation which forms a harmonious whole with the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK is displaying its invincible might thanks to the unique Songun policy of Kim Jong Il, they pointed out, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Workers' Party and people of Korea have achieved wonderful successes in increasing national defense power and building a great prosperous powerful nation, while opening a turning phase in accomplishing the cause of national reunification.

Functions Held Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Functions were held in different countries on the occasions of the 6th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 58th anniversary of the WPK.
 A meeting took place in Rome on Sept. 26 under the co-sponsorship of the Movement for Peace and Socialism, the Unified Communist Party, the Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea of Italy and the Nino Pasti International Fund. Roberto Gabriele, general secretary of the Movement for Peace and Socialism, in a speech said that Kim Jong Il has built the WPK into singleheartedly united strong ranks of Juche type and led socialist Korea to victory, carrying forward and developing the revolutionary cause started by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that under the leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK would surely prove successful in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and carrying out the cause of national reunification and in the nuclear stand-off with the U.S., he said that the movement would always extend firm solidarity to the WPK in all its policies and measures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lectures were given on Sept. 29 by the Juche Philosophy Study Committee of India, the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of University of Kinshasa in Democratic Congo, and at Federico Villareal University of Peru and the Fitirabitra Bahtera Pratama Company of Indonesia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at a lecture given in India. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Abani Roy, secretary of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of India, and Ratigo Oral, deputy director for foreign Relations of the Secretariat of the National Movement of Uganda, in their statements said that under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK has covered a road of victory and made progress in the struggle for national reunification even under the ever-changing situation.

German Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- German Ambassador to the DPRK Doris Hertrampf hosted a reception at the embassy on Friday evening on the occasion of the national day of Germany.
 Present there on invitation were Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Kim Yong Sul, vice-minister of Foreign Trade who is chairman of the DPRK Committee for the Promotion of External Economic Cooperation, Sim Tong Gil, vice-minister of Culture, Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries who is chairperson of the Korea-Germany Friendship Association, officials concerned, diplomatic envoys and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there

Japanese Diplomatic Chief's Remarks under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Japan's diplomatic chief recently pulled up the DPRK over the issue of abduction and nuclear development in a speech made at the 58th session of the UN General Assembly. And Motomura, Japanese ambassador to the United Nations, said that he never thinks that the issue of abduction has been solved.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today says in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of abducting several Japanese about which the Japanese government talked much has already been settled by the adoption of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration in September last year. Lurking behind the row kicked up by Japan over the issue of abduction is a sinister intention to internationalize this issue in a bid to tarnish the image of the DPRK in the international arena and evade its responsibility to liquidate its past at any cost under the pretext of the issue. 
 The Japanese chief executive admitted to Japan's crimes in the past and committed himself to redeem it in the declaration. The Japanese government is, therefore, obliged to honestly reflect on the hideous criminal acts the Japanese imperialists committed in Korea in the past and opt for redeeming the crimes before talking about the issue of abduction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's liquidation of its past is the core of the declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan is in a position to remain true to the spirit of the declaration and implement it, it should, first of all, redeem its past. The normalization of relations between the DPRK and Japan can never be expected nor can it happen without Japan's liquidation of its past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's negative attitude towards the issue of redeeming its past can not be construed otherwise than its refusal to respect the declaration and fulfil its obligation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's liquidation of its past is not a simple humanitarian issue that it may sidestep but a serious political and international issue and historical task pending a solution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Japan relations will never improve unless Japan redresses its past including the probe into the truth behind the unprecedented crimes it committed against the Korean people and its honest apology and compensation for them.

Preservation of Juche Character and National Identity Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Thoroughly preserving the Juche character and national identity in the efforts to achieve the country's reunification is a sure guarantee for accomplishing the cause of reunification, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is the truth of history as its justness and vitality have been proved in the days of the leadership provided by the Workers' Party of Korea for national reunification.
 The Juche-oriented line and policies for national reunification advanced by President Kim Il Sung and the immortal feats performed by him in the cause of national reunification are firmly upheld and glorified by leader Kim Jong Il, who has confidently carried forward the idea and cause of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He clarified that preserving the Juche character and national identity in carving out the destiny of the country and the nation presents itself as a principled requirement for ensuring the sovereignty and independence of the country and its progress and the prosperity of the nation. He formulated the line and policies for national reunification advanced by the President including the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo based on the Juche character and national identity as the three charters of national reunification, thus providing important guidelines that all Koreans desirous of reunification should hold fast to. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nation's cause of reunification has greeted its best days. This is ascribable to the pro-reunification patriotic leadership of Kim Jong Il who, considering all problems from a Juche-oriented viewpoint and solving them on the principle of national independence, has steered the cause of reunification on the basis of the excellent national character.
